Kabul, Sep 19 ( Prensa Latina) At least 55 Afghan farmers were victims of US aerial bombings in Wazir-Tangi, Nangarhar province, local legislator Zabihullah Zmarai said today. Twenty-five farmers died as a result and the rest are wounded, many of them mutilated, noted the source. Zmarai stressed that the attack took place in an agricultural area when villagers were harvesting pine nuts, an edible seed traditional in the diet of this country. From January through July, 363 civilians were killed in Afghanistan, among them 89 children, double the number of deaths in the same stage of 2018, according to official figures from the UN Assistance Mission in Afghanistan (UNAMA).